TY  - JOUR
TI  - A Convergence Theorem for Competitive Bidding with Differential Information
AU  - Milgrom, Paul R.
AB  - [This paper investigates the behavior of the winning bid in a sealed bid tender auction where each bidder has private information. With an appropriate concept of value, the winning bid will converge in probability to the value of the object auction (as the number of bidders grow large) if and only if a certain information condition is satisfied. In particular, it is not necessary for any bidder to know the value at the time the bids are submitted. These results bear on the relationship between price and value and on the aggregation of private information by the auction mechanism.]
C1  - Full publication date: May, 1979
